Highlighter
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
A plugin for Croogo CMS for code syntax highlighting.


REQUIREMENTS
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    - Requires Croogo 1.3.2 or above.
    - It is recommended that you have the option of editing the HTML content of your posts.
      TinyMCE plugin already does this trick.

HOW TO USE
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    1. Log in to admin panel
    2. Go to Extensions > Plugins page
    3. Upload the zip file (available here)
    4. Click on tick/cross icon of 'highlighter' for activating or deactivating the plugin


CREDITS
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Author       : Jacob 'jacmoe' Moen
Author Email : jacmoe@jacmoe.dk
Author Url   : http://www.jacmoe.dk/

This plugin uses third-party software for syntax highlighting.
Alex Gorbatchev's SyntaxHighlighter. http://alexgorbatchev.com/SyntaxHighlighter/


EXAMPLE
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
After the plugin was activated, go and create a new post. Use HTML button on the TinyMCE WYSIWYG editor
and paste the following code:

        <pre class="brush: php;">class HighlighterActivation {

            public function beforeActivation(&amp;$controller) {
                 return true;
            }
            public function onActivation(&amp;$controller) {}
            public function beforeDeactivation(&amp;$controller) {
                  return true;
            }
            public function onDeactivation(&amp;$controller) {}


        }
        </pre>

Save your post and enjoy your new syntax highlighting functionality!